<Link id="l02079" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2079"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// DWARF discriminators distinguish identical file locations between</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02080" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2080"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// instructions that are on different basic blocks.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02081" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2081"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02082" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2082"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// There are 3 components stored in discriminator, from lower bits:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02083" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2083"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02084" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2084"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Base discriminator: assigned by AddDiscriminators pass to identify IRs</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02085" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2085"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///                     that are defined by the same source line, but</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02086" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2086"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///                     different basic blocks.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02087" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2087"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Duplication factor: assigned by optimizations that will scale down</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02088" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2088"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///                     the execution frequency of the original IR.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02089" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2089"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Copy Identifier: assigned by optimizations that clones the IR.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02090" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2090"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///                  Each copy of the IR will be assigned an identifier.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02091" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2091"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02092" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2092"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Encoding:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02093" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2093"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2094"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The above 3 components are encoded into a 32bit unsigned integer in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2095"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// order. If the lowest bit is 1, the current component is empty, and the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2096"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// next component will start in the next bit. Otherwise, the current</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02097" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2097"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// component is non-empty, and its content starts in the next bit. The</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2098"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// value of each components is either 5 bit or 12 bit: if the 7th bit</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2099"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// is 0, the bit 2~6 (5 bits) are used to represent the component; if the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2100"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// 7th bit is 1, the bit 2~6 (5 bits) and 8~14 (7 bits) are combined to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2101"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// represent the component. Thus, the number of bits used for a component</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2102"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// is either 0 (if it and all the next components are empty); 1 - if it is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2103"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// empty; 7 - if its value is up to and including 31 (lsb and msb are both</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02104" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2104"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// 0); or 14, if its value is up to and including 0x1ff. Note that the last</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2105"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// component is also capped at 0x1ff, even in the case when both first</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2106"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// components are 0, and we&#39;d technically have 29 bits available.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2107"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2108"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// For precise control over the data being encoded in the discriminator,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2109"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// use encodeDiscriminator/decodeDiscriminator.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02110" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2110"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02111" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2111"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">inline</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> getDiscriminator() </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02112" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2112"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02113" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2113"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// For the regular discriminator, it stands for all empty components if all</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02114" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2114"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the lowest 3 bits are non-zero and all higher 29 bits are unused(zero by</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02115" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2115"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// default). Here we fully leverage the higher 29 bits for pseudo probe use.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02116" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2116"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// This is the format:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02117" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2117"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &#91;2:0&#93; - 7</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02118" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2118"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &#91;31:3&#93; - pseudo probe fields guaranteed to be non-zero as a whole</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02119" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2119"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// So if the lower 3 bits is non-zero and the others has at least one</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02120" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2120"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// non-zero bit, it guarantees to be a pseudo probe discriminator</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02121" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2121" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dilocation/#a1d5bbfbe6fc9f92e22bf16cb1c2dc110"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">inline</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dilocation/#a1d5bbfbe6fc9f92e22bf16cb1c2dc110">isPseudoProbeDiscriminator</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> Discriminator) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02122" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2122"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> ((Discriminator &amp; 0x7) == 0x7) &amp;&amp; (Discriminator &amp; 0xFFFFFFF8);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02123" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2123"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02124" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2124"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2125"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Returns a new DILocation with updated \\p Discriminator.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2132"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">inline</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> std::optional&lt;const DILocation &#42;&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2134"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2135"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Returns the duplication factor stored in the discriminator, or 1 if no</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2136"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// duplication factor (or 0) is encoded.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2140"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">inline</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dilocation/#af69ab81ed05b68f90320107086d351f6">getCopyIdentifier</a>() </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02145" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2145"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Returns a new DILocation with duplication factor \\p DF &#42; current</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02146" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2146"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// duplication factor encoded in the discriminator. The current duplication</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02151" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2151"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02152" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2152"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// When two instructions are combined into a single instruction we also</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02153" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2153"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// need to combine the original locations into a single location.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02154" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2154"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// When the locations are the same we can use either location.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02155" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2155"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// When they differ, we need a third location which is distinct from either.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02156" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2156"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// If they share a common scope, use this scope and compare the line/column</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02157" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2157"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// pair of the locations with the common scope:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2158"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// &#42; if both match, keep the line and column;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02159" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2159"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// &#42; if only the line number matches, keep the line and set the column as 0;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2160"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// &#42; otherwise set line and column as 0</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2161"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// If they do not share a common scope the location is ambiguous and can&#39;t be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2162"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// represented in a line entry. In this case, set line and column as 0 and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2163"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// use the scope of any location.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2164"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2165"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\p LocA \\p LocB: The locations to be merged.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2166"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dilocation">DILocation</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dilocation/#a78cc51c415c7e64b5efe2c8458fbd35a">getMergedLocation</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dilocation">DILocation</a> &#42;LocA, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dilocation">DILocation</a> &#42;LocB);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2167"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2168"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Try to combine the vector of locations passed as input in a single one.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2169"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// This function applies getMergedLocation() repeatedly left-to-right.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2170"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2171"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\p Locs: The locations to be merged.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2172"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dilocation">DILocation</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dilocation/#a30a7ce961d5d90ff2fb6c9cee4576e5a">getMergedLocations</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef&lt;DILocation &#42;&gt;</a> Locs);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2173"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2175"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// (i.e. zero out the (B+1)-th and above bits for D (B is 0-base).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2176"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Example: an input of (0x1FF, 7) returns 0xFF.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2177" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dilocation/#aa9609cd613f944e461d2d2b83c4132c4"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dilocation/#aa9609cd613f944e461d2d2b83c4132c4">getMaskedDiscriminator</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#a6a9f043784cf87001c84980afa76da82">D</a>, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a>) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2179"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2200"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/pseudoprobedwarfdiscriminator/#a5db4061b62e740850ad71806b1dbd60e">PseudoProbeDwarfDiscriminator::extractProbeIndex</a>(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#a6a9f043784cf87001c84980afa76da82">D</a>);</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l03123" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3123"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03124" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3124"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Computes a fragment, bit-extract operation if needed, and new constant</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3125"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// offset to describe a part of a variable covered by some memory.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3126"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3127"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The memory region starts at:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3128"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   \\p SliceStart + \\p SliceOffsetInBits</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3129"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// And is size:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3130"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   \\p SliceSizeInBits</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3131"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3132"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The location of the existing variable fragment \\p VarFrag is:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3133"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   \\p DbgPtr + \\p DbgPtrOffsetInBits + \\p DbgExtractOffsetInBits.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3134"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3135"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// It is intended that these arguments are derived from a debug record:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3136"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - \\p DbgPtr is the (single) DIExpression operand.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3137"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - \\p DbgPtrOffsetInBits is the constant offset applied to \\p DbgPtr.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3138"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - \\p DbgExtractOffsetInBits is the offset from a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3139"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   DW&#95;OP&#95;LLVM&#95;bit&#95;extract&#95;&#91;sz&#93;ext operation.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3140"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3141"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Results and return value:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3142"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - Return false if the result can&#39;t be calculated for any reason.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3143"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - \\p Result is set to nullopt if the intersect equals \\p VarFarg.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03144" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3144"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - \\p Result contains a zero-sized fragment if there&#39;s no intersect.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03145" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3145"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// - \\p OffsetFromLocationInBits is set to the difference between the first</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03146" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3146"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   bit of the variable location and the first bit of the slice. The</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03147" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3147"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   magnitude of a negative value therefore indicates the number of bits</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03148" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3148"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   into the variable fragment that the memory region begins.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03149" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3149"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03150" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3150"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// We don&#39;t pass in a debug record directly to get the constituent parts</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03151" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3151"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// and offsets because different debug records store the information in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03152" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3152"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// different places (dbg&#95;assign has two DIExpressions - one contains the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03153" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3153"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// fragment info for the entire intrinsic).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03154" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3154"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/diexpression/#a4ea8623be899e029827af260965c860d">calculateFragmentIntersect</a>(</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03155" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3155"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/datalayout">DataLayout</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/arm/armslshardening-cpp/#ad467c4ab9119043f9b7750ab986be61a">DL</a>, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42;SliceStart, uint64&#95;t SliceOffsetInBits,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03156" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3156"><Highlight kind="normal">      uint64&#95;t SliceSizeInBits, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42;DbgPtr, int64&#95;t DbgPtrOffsetInBits,</Highlight></CodeLine>
